GNOME

Ability Score Increase: INT +1
Size: Small
Speed: 25 feet
Darkvision
Gnome Cunning: Advantage on all INT, WIS, and CHA saving throws against magic
Languages: Common, Gnomish

SUBRACES: FOREST GNOME AND ROCK GNOME

ROCK GNOME
Ability Score Increase: CON +1
Artificer's Lore: INT check related to magic items, alchemical objects, or technological devices - add twice your proficiency bonus.
Tinker: Proficiency with artisan's tools (tinker's tools). Using tools you can spend 1 hour and 10 gp worth of materials to construct a Tiny clockwork device (AC 5, 1 hp). The device ceases to function after 24 hours (unless you spend 1 hour repairing it to keep the device functioning), or when you use your action to dismantle it; at that time, you can reclaim the materials used to create it. You can have up to three such devices active at a time. 

Clockwork Toy: 
This toy is a clockwork animal, monster, or person, such as a frog, mouse, bird, dragon, or soldier. When placed on the ground, they toy moves 5 feet across the ground on each of your turns in a random direction.
Fire Starter:  
The device produces a miniature flame, which you can use to light a candle, torch, or campfire. Using the device requires your action.
Music Box:
When opened, this box plays a single song at a moderate volume. The box stops playing when it reaches the song's end or when it is closed. 

FOREST GNOME
Ability Score Increase: DEX +1
Natural Illusionist: Know minor illusion cantrip, use INT for spell casting ability.
Speak with small beasts: Communicate simple ideas with small or smaller beasts. 
